# /pr-create — Create Pull Request

## Purpose
Create GitHub pull requests with descriptive title, structured body, and test checklist.

## Pre-checks
1. Verify `gh` authentication (`gh auth status`)
2. Verify NOT on main/master branch
3. Verify unpushed commits exist (`git log origin/HEAD..HEAD`)

## Process
1. Detect base branch (explicit argument or repo default branch)
2. List branch commits (`git log base..HEAD --oneline`)
3. Generate title:
   - Single commit: use commit message
   - Multiple: summarize the change set
   - Max 70 characters
4. Generate body from template
5. Push if needed (`git push -u origin HEAD`)
6. Create PR via `gh pr create`

## Body Template
```markdown
## Summary
- Bullet points describing the main changes

## Changes
{{#each modules}}
- [ ] `{{name}}`: (describe changes in this module)
{{/each}}

## Test plan
- [ ] Unit tests passing
- [ ] Lint clean
- [ ] Build clean

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)
```

## Flags
- `--draft`: create as draft PR
- `--base <branch>`: specify base branch
- `--title <title>`: custom title
{{/if}}
